# Design Tokens & Styling Patterns

## Approach

This project uses **Tailwind CSS v4** with Shadcn/UI. Styles are applied as utility classes directly on JSX elements. There are no separate `*.styles.tsx` files — all styling is inline via `className`.

Use `cn()` from `@/lib/utils` to conditionally merge classes:

```tsx
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';

<div className={cn('rounded-lg px-4 py-2', isActive && 'bg-primary text-primary-foreground')} />
```

## CSS Custom Properties

Design tokens are defined in `app/globals.css` using CSS custom properties. Always reference them — never hardcode raw values.

### Color Tokens (oklch-based)

The color system is built on a single `--base-hue` variable (262.04 — violet/purple):

| Token                     | Usage                              |
| ------------------------- | ---------------------------------- |
| `--background`            | Page background                    |
| `--foreground`            | Primary text                       |
| `--card`                  | Card/panel backgrounds             |
| `--card-foreground`       | Text on cards                      |
| `--primary`               | Brand color (violet)               |
| `--primary-foreground`    | Text on primary backgrounds        |
| `--secondary`             | Subtle backgrounds                 |
| `--secondary-background`  | Darker background variant          |
| `--muted`                 | Muted surface                      |
| `--muted-foreground`      | Muted text                         |
| `--accent`                | Accent surface                     |
| `--border`                | Border color                       |
| `--link`                  | Hyperlink color                    |

### Radius Tokens

| Token          | Value                   |
| -------------- | ----------------------- |
| `--radius`     | Base radius variable    |
| `rounded-sm`   | `calc(var(--radius) - 4px)` |
| `rounded-md`   | `calc(var(--radius) - 2px)` |
| `rounded-lg`   | `var(--radius)`         |
| `rounded-xl`   | `calc(var(--radius) + 4px)` |

### Typography Tokens

| Token               | Usage                   |
| ------------------- | ----------------------- |
| `--font-display`    | Display/heading font    |
| `--font-serif`      | Serif body font         |
| `--font-mono`       | Monospace font          |
| `--font-mono-code`  | Code blocks             |
| `--font-signature`  | Signature / handwriting |

Apply via Tailwind:
```tsx
<h1 className="font-display text-4xl tracking-tight" />
<p className="font-serif text-base leading-7" />
<code className="font-mono-code text-sm" />
```

## Tailwind Utility Patterns

### Glassmorphism

Used for floating panels, the header, cards overlaid on content:

```tsx
<div
  className="rounded-xl border border-muted bg-card/50 px-3 py-2"
  style={{
    backdropFilter: 'blur(var(--blur, 12px)) saturate(var(--saturate, 1.15))',
  }}
/>
```

CSS variables `--blur`, `--saturate`, and `--opacity` are available globally from `globals.css`.

### oklch Transparency

Use `oklch()` with the CSS relative color syntax for transparent variants:

```css
/* In CSS or inline style */
background-color: oklch(from var(--foreground) l c h / 0.08);
border-color: oklch(from var(--border) l c h / 0.5);
```

In Tailwind, use arbitrary values:
```tsx
<div className="bg-[oklch(from_var(--foreground)_l_c_h_/_0.08)]" />
```

## Dark Mode

Dark mode uses the `.dark` class on `<html>` (managed by `next-themes`). The `@custom-variant dark` in `globals.css` maps it to the `dark:` prefix.

```tsx
<div className="bg-background text-foreground dark:bg-secondary-background" />
```

## Motion Tokens

Defined in `app/globals.css` `:root`. Use in CSS transitions or pass as numeric seconds to Motion:

| Token | Value | When to use |
|-------|-------|-------------|
| `--duration-instant` | 50ms | Imperceptible state changes |
| `--duration-fast` | 150ms | Micro-interactions, hover |
| `--duration-moderate` | 300ms | Standard enter/exit |
| `--duration-slow` | 500ms | Deliberate reveals |
| `--duration-deliberate` | 700ms | Dramatic exits (splash screen) |
| `--ease-standard` | `cubic-bezier(0.2, 0, 0, 1)` | Default transitions |
| `--ease-enter` | `cubic-bezier(0, 0, 0.2, 1)` | Elements entering viewport |
| `--ease-exit` | `cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 1, 1)` | Elements leaving |
| `--ease-bounce` | `cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.56, 0.64, 1)` | Springy reveals |

```tsx
// Motion transition using tokens (convert ms → seconds)
transition={{ duration: 0.3, ease: [0.2, 0, 0, 1] }}  // --duration-moderate + --ease-standard

// CSS transition using tokens
style={{ transition: 'opacity var(--duration-fast) var(--ease-standard)' }}
```

## Elevation Tokens

| Token | Usage |
|-------|-------|
| `--shadow-sm` | Subtle card lift |
| `--shadow-md` | Dropdowns, floating panels |
| `--shadow-lg` | Modals, sheets |

```tsx
<div style={{ boxShadow: 'var(--shadow-md)' }} />
```

## Key Principles

- **Never hardcode colors** — use `var(--*)` tokens or Tailwind semantic classes
- **Never hardcode spacing** — use Tailwind spacing scale (`p-4`, `gap-2`, etc.)
- **No separate style files** — Tailwind utilities go directly in JSX `className`
- **Use `cn()`** from `@/lib/utils` for all conditional class merging
- **oklch everywhere** — use `oklch()` for transparency and color manipulation
- **Shadcn components** are pre-styled; customize via `className` props, not by editing `components/ui/`
